 [1] Electron Beam      Relativistic e⁻, 0.5–4 GeV, variable & repeatable
 [2] Cherenkov Det.     Beam tagger; confirms e⁻ passage; fast reference signal
 [3] Tungsten (W)       Bremsstrahlung target; Z=74; 2.5 X₀ ≈ 8.75 mm thick
 [4] Collimator         Shapes γ beam into narrow pencil; reduces path-length uncertainty
 [5] Graphite (C)       Compton scatterer; Z=6; Ø2cm×2cm rod; tilted 45° to beam
 [6] Scintillator t₁    First timestamp; decay time 2–3 ns; starts TOF measurement
 [7] DWC                Delay Wire Chamber; reconstructs (x,y) track → θ and L
 [8] Scintillator t₂    Second timestamp; Δt = t₂ − t₁ = time-of-flight
